Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getHierFlowMode(25.10)                                  getHierFlowMode(25.10)

Name
       getHierFlowMode  - Displays the following information about a specified
       budgeting mode parameter in the Innovus log file  and  in  the  Innovus
       console

Syntax
       getHierFlowMode

       [-help]

       [-budgets]

       [-quiet]

       [-nonDefault]

       Displays the following information about a specified budgeting mode pa-
       rameter in the Innovus log file and in the Innovus console.

              * Parameter name

              * Current value

              * Type (Boolean, string, and so on)

              * Whether the current value was set by user

       If  you  do  not specify a parameter, the software displays information
       for all the getHierFlowMode parameters.

Parameters
       <-parameter_names>
              Displays information for the specified parameters. You can spec-
              ify one or more parameters.

              See setHierFlowMode for descriptions of the budgeting mode para-
              meters you can specify.

       -quiet Displays the current settings for the  specified  parameters  in
              Tcl list format only.

              If  you specify -quiet without any parameters, the software dis-
              plays the current settings of all setHierFlowMode parameters  in
              Tcl list format.

Examples
              * The  following  command  displays  the current setting for the
                -budgets parameter:

                getHierFlowMode -budgets

                The software displays the following information:

                -budgets none         # enums={accurate preliminary none}, de-
                fault=none

                none

              * The following command displays the  current  setting  for  the
                -nonDefault parameter in Tcl list format:

                getHierFlowMode -nonDefault

                The software displays the following information:

                <CMD> getHierFlowMode -nonDefault

Related Information
              * setHierFlowMode

              * The Timing Budgeting chapter of the User Guide document

